channel.title: My server wont go live
channel.description:
Hello, I need some help with getting my server live for others to play. I have JDK 6, I have a registered host on No-ip, all my firewalls allow my server, I port forwarded my server, and I can log on with localhost, but cant connect when using my actual server IP (others cant either) <- sorry about lack of periods I made my server live on another computer, but I am getting rid of that computer soon. I did everything I did on my computer that RSPS worked on. .. Additional info: The computer that worked was a windows XP, computer Im using is a Windows Vista... I use Liksy (spllin?) router. SOZ bout bein a nub.. :o
And because I know it's comming, heres how I portforwarded... Not tryin to break any rules Name.........start.....end........tcp.......ip......enabled
RSPS 43594 43594 tcp 102 yes

server TCP | 43594 - 43594 | TCP | 192.168..__ | 43594 - 43594
server UDP | 43594 - 43594 | UDP | 192.168..__ | 43594 - 43594

i can’t log in with my ip on my sever but other people can[you have to use localhost]. it’s just like that.[/quote]
Isnt that the same as just selecting both as an option for tcp/udp
